mods:mods.mods:abstract: Sher Afzal Khan is Higher Education Trainer, learning facilitator and working as Chief Librarian Bahria University, Pakistan. He provides trainings on Library Automation, Open Source Software i.e. KOHA, DSpace, Green Stone and LIMS in various universities of Pakistan. He is also country representative of DSpace Institutional Repository Software. He automates and helps different libraries and library professional in automation. He also win US$ 30000/- from China Government for Bahria University. He has also conducted series of workshops, trainings in different universities and organizations of Pakistan including Bahria University Islamabad and Karachi, Government College University (GCU) Lahore, University of Malakand, PASTIC, NCRD, SDPI, PARD and HEC Islamabad.

Il saggio di Gorman, che riproponiamo volentieri ai lettori di “Biblioteche oggi”, costituisce un’importante riflessione sull’utilizzo dei metadata e sulla loro efficacia nel ricupero delle risorse elettroniche (ER) disponibili in rete; significativa è la correlazione fra la problematica del controllo bibliografico delle ER remote e la pianificazione del processo della loro selezione.
